We are continually working on changing the incentive mechanism so that we are incentivizing GPUs that users actually want from our platform. This comes with 2 big updates.

First is emissions pooling. Now, instead of being able to add unlimited GPUs of a single type and getting increasing incentive for it, we are now restricting total incentive per GPU type. 

You can see the current GPU incentive pools here: https://github.com/Datura-ai/compute-subnet/blob/8afc1f2be075e0b80d32ff5b261c2de2153c0f95/neurons/validators/src/services/const.py#L5
```python
GPU_MODEL_RATES = {
    "NVIDIA B200": .05,
    "NVIDIA H200": .55,
    "NVIDIA H100 80GB HBM3": .10,
    "NVIDIA H100 NVL": .01,
    "NVIDIA H100 PCIe": .01,
    "NVIDIA H800 80GB HBM3": 0.02,
    "NVIDIA H800 NVL": 0.01,
    "NVIDIA H800 PCIe": 0.01,
    "NVIDIA GeForce RTX 5090": 0.025,
    "NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4090": 0.05,
    "NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4090 D": 0.02,
    "NVIDIA RTX 4000 Ada Generation": 0.005,
    "NVIDIA RTX 6000 Ada Generation": 0.01,
    "NVIDIA L4": 0.01,
    "NVIDIA L40S": 0.01,
    "NVIDIA L40": 0.01,
    "NVIDIA RTX 2000 Ada Generation": 0.001,
    "NVIDIA A100 80GB PCIe": 0.01,
    "NVIDIA A100-SXM4-80GB": 0.05,
    "NVIDIA RTX A6000": 0.009,
    "NVIDIA RTX A5000": 0.002,
    "NVIDIA RTX A4500": 0.002,
    "NVIDIA RTX A4000": 0.002,
    "NVIDIA A40": 0.002,
    "NVIDIA A30": 0.002,
    "NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3090": 0.02,
}```

This means, that H200s are currently awarded 55% of the total miner incentive of the subnet, no matter how many H200s actually exist on the subnet. They will share 55% of total miner incentive.

These pools normalize to 1 and it is how we decided to initialize the split. 

We are also making these pools dynamic. We have a formula R / I which is revenue per incentive given to each GPU type. 

If this value is high, we will increase the incentive for a certain GPU type. If it is low, we will decrease it. The goal is for us to maximize revenue  per incentive, until eventually revenue is greater than incentive, meaning the subnet is profitable. 

Next, we have recently been playing around with dynamic pricing. This means that if demand for one GPU type is very high compared to supply, we will increase the price for the remaining machines, and vice versa. 

We are working very hard in the background on updates and trying to make the subnet profitable. Please leave your feedback on the recent updates in this channel

Here's detailed formula for pools dynamic: https://github.com/Datura-ai/compute-subnet/blob/main/neurons/validators/src/clients/compute_client.py#L536

Formula: 
```
I = I + delta * (R - I)
```

Here, `R` is the revenue per GPU types that the celium get. 

Current period of updating this is per hour.
